<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 1431/82 of 18 May 1982 laying down special measures for peas, field beans and sweet lupins (9), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 1485/85 (10), and in particular Article 3 (5) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 18. mai 1982. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 1431/82, millega n&auml;hakse ette herne, p&otilde;ldoa ja maguslupiiniga seotud erimeetmed, viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 1485/85, eriti selle artikli 3 l&otilde;iget 5, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 1677/85 of 11 June 1985 on monetary compensatory amounts in agriculture (11), and in particular Article 12 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 11. juuni 1985. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 1677/85 kursikompensatsioonide kohta p&otilde;llumajanduses, eriti selle artiklit 12, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas numerous provisions in Community agricultural Regulations require that a security be given to ensure payment of a sum due if an obligation is not met; whereas, however, experience has shown that this requirement is in practice interpreted in widely differing fashions; whereas, therefore, in order to avoid unequal competitive conditions, the requirement should be more fully defined; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: &uuml;henduse p&otilde;llumajandusm&auml;&auml;ruste mitmete s&auml;tete kohaselt tuleb esitada tagatis, mis on vajalik, et tagada kohustuse t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmise korral etten&auml;htud summa maksmine; kogemused on siiski n&auml;idanud, et praktikas t&otilde;lgendatakse seda n&otilde;uet suuresti erineval viisil; seep&auml;rast tuleks ebav&otilde;rdsete konkurentsitingimuste v&auml;ltimiseks k&otilde;nealune n&otilde;ue t&auml;psemalt m&auml;&auml;ratleda; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in particulaf, the form of the security should be defined; </inglise>
<eesti> eelk&otilde;ige tuleks m&auml;&auml;ratleda tagatise vorm; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas many provisions in Community agricultural Regulations provide that the security given is forfeited if any obligation secured is breached, without making any distinction between breaches of fundamental and of secondary or subordinate obligations; whereas in the interests of equity a distinction should be drawn between the consequences of breaching a fundamental obligation and the consequences of breaching a secondary or subordinate one; whereas, in particular, provision should be made, where permissible, for forfeiture of only a part of the security where the fundamental obligation is in fact met but the deadline set for meeting it has been slightly exceeded, or when a secondary or subordinate obligation is not met; </inglise>
<eesti> mitmete &uuml;henduse p&otilde;llumajandusm&auml;&auml;ruste s&auml;tetega n&auml;hakse ette, et tagatisega seotud kohustuse rikkumise korral j&auml;&auml;dakse tagatisest ilma, kusjuures ei eristata p&otilde;hi- v&otilde;i k&otilde;rval- v&otilde;i allkohustuste rikkumisi; v&otilde;rdv&auml;&auml;rsuse huvides tuleks vahet teha p&otilde;hikohustuse v&otilde;i k&otilde;rvalkohustuse v&otilde;i allkohustuse rikkumisest tulenevate tagaj&auml;rgede vahel; eelk&otilde;ige tuleks v&otilde;imaluse korral ette n&auml;ha, et tagatisest j&auml;&auml;dakse ilma ainult osaliselt, kui p&otilde;hikohustus on t&auml;idetud, kuid selle t&auml;itmise t&auml;htaega on veidi &uuml;letatud, v&otilde;i kui ei ole t&auml;idetud k&otilde;rvalkohustust v&otilde;i allkohustust; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas no distinction between the consequences of failure to meet an obligation should be made based on whether or not an advance payment has been received; whereas, accordingly, secufrities given against advances are covered by separate rules; </inglise>
<eesti> kohustuse t&auml;itmataj&auml;tmisest tulenevaid tagaj&auml;rgi ei tuleks eristada selle p&otilde;hjal, kas ettemaks on k&auml;tte saadud v&otilde;i mitte; ettemaksu vastu antavaid tagatisi reguleeritakse eraldi eeskirjadega; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the costs of lodging a security, incurred by both the party giving the security and the competent authority, may be out of proportion to the sum whose payment the security guarantees if that sum is below a certain limit; whereas competent authorities must therefore have the right to waive the requirement of a security for payment of a sum below that limit; whereas, further, a competent authority should be empowered to waive the requirement of a security where the nature of the person required to meet the obligations makes that requirement unnecessary; </inglise>
